# Test Conventions (Vitest + RTL)

## File Naming and Location

- Unit/integration tests: `<subject>.test.ts` / `<subject>.test.tsx` co-located next to the file under test.
- Backend API tests: `src/test/<subject>.test.ts`.
- E2E: `e2e/<feature>.test.ts` using Playwright.

## Test Structure

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — describe + it, clear intent
describe('TodoService', () => {
  it('returns all todos for a given user', async () => { ... });
  it('throws 404 when todo does not exist', async () => { ... });
});

// ❌ BAD — flat test function, no grouping
test('todo service works', async () => { ... });
```

## Frontend — React Testing Library

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — tests implementation detail (internal state)
expect(component.state.isLoading).toBe(true);

// ❌ BAD — fireEvent doesn't simulate real browser events
fireEvent.click(button);

// ✅ GOOD — test what the user sees/does
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
const user = userEvent.setup();
await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /add todo/i }));
expect(screen.getByText('My new todo')).toBeInTheDocument();
```

## Backend — Supertest

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — use supertest against the Express app factory
import { createApp } from '../app';
const app = createApp(testDb);
const res = await request(app).post('/api/todos').send({ title: 'Test' });
expect(res.status).toBe(201);
```

## Rules

- Prefer `getByRole` > `getByLabelText` > `getByText` > `getByTestId` (last resort).
- Never assert on CSS classes or internal component state.
- Each `it` block should have exactly one logical assertion group.
- Use `vi.fn()` for mocks; reset with `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach`.
- Backend tests must use an **in-memory SQLite** test database, never the dev DB.
